## Amplitude Analytics API Platform

Amplitude provides a comprehensive suite of REST APIs for analytics data ingestion, user management, data export, and platform administration. The platform serves as a complete analytics solution with APIs spanning data collection, user behavior analysis, cohort management, and compliance operations.

## Product Architecture and Relationships

The Amplitude API ecosystem is structured around several core functional areas:

**Data Ingestion Layer:**
- **HTTP V2 API** (`/2/httpapi`) - Primary server-to-server event ingestion endpoint
- **Batch Event Upload API** - Bulk data upload with 20MB payload limits and rate limiting
- **Identify API** (`/identify`) - User property management and User ID to Device ID mapping
- **Group Identify API** (`/groupidentify`) - Group-level property management for Accounts add-on
- **Attribution API** (`/attribution`) - Mobile advertising attribution tracking with 72-hour attribution windows

**Data Access and Export:**
- **Export API** (`/api/2/export`) - Raw event data export with 4GB limits and zipped JSON output
- **Dashboard REST API** - Analytics query results including funnels, retention, segmentation, and revenue metrics
- **User Profile API** (`profile-api.amplitude.com/v1/userprofile`) - Real-time user profile data with recommendations and computed properties

**User and Cohort Management:**
- **Behavioral Cohorts API** (v3/v5) - Asynchronous cohort operations with S3 integration and 2M user limits
- **User Mapping API** (`/usermap`) - Cross-project user aliasing for Portfolio add-on
- **SCIM 2.0 API** - Enterprise user provisioning and group management

**Data Enhancement and Configuration:**
- **Lookup Table API** (v1/v3) - CSV-based property augmentation with 100MB/1M row limits
- **Taxonomy API** - Enterprise event schema management with property classifications
- **Chart Annotations API** (`/api/2/annotations`) - Programmatic chart annotation management
- **Releases API** (`/api/2/release`) - Product release tracking and deployment integration

**Compliance and Privacy:**
- **User Privacy API** (`/api/2/deletions/users`) - GDPR/CCPA user data deletion with 30-day scheduling
- **CCPA DSAR API** - Data Subject Access Request processing with asynchronous workflows

**Monitoring and Operations:**
- **Event Streaming Metrics API** - Delivery metrics for event streams with 90-day retention

## Key Nomenclature and Definitions

**Core Identifiers:**
- `amplitude_id` - Amplitude's internal user identifier
- `user_id` - Customer-defined user identifier
- `device_id` - Device-specific identifier
- `session_id` - Session tracking identifier
- `insert_id` - Event deduplication identifier

**Mobile Attribution IDs:**
- `idfa` - iOS Identifier for Advertiser
- `idfv` - iOS Identifier for Vendor
- `adid` - Google Android Advertising ID
- `android_app_set_id` - Android App Set ID

**Property Operations:**
- `$set`, `$setOnce`, `$add`, `$append`, `$prepend`, `$unset` - Standard property modification operations
- `$preInsert`, `$postInsert`, `$remove` - Advanced array manipulation operations
- `$identify`, `$groupidentify` - Special event types for property updates

**API Parameters:**
- `api_key` - Project-level authentication
- `app_id` - Project identifier
- `group_type`/`group_value` - Group identification for Accounts add-on
- `sync_id` - Event streaming destination identifier
- `cohort_id` - Behavioral cohort identifier

**Rate Limiting and Constraints:**
- EPS (Events Per Second) - Rate limiting metric
- EPDS/EPUS - Events Per Device/User per Second
- Cost-based rate limiting - Enterprise API throttling model

## Ecosystem Integration

The Amplitude API platform integrates with broader analytics and marketing technology stacks through several mechanisms:

**Authentication Models:**
- HTTP Basic Authentication (most APIs)
- API Key authentication (ingestion APIs)
- Secret Key authentication (User Profile API)
- SCIM Key authentication (SCIM API)

**Regional Data Residency:**
- Standard endpoints: `api2.amplitude.com`, `api.amplitude.com`
- EU residency: `api.eu.amplitude.com`
- Specialized endpoints: `profile-api.amplitude.com`, `data-api.amplitude.com`

**Enterprise Features:**
- Portfolio add-on for cross-project user mapping
- Accounts add-on for group-level analytics
- Growth/Enterprise plans for advanced cohort operations
- Activation plan for User Profile API access

**Integration Patterns:**
- Asynchronous workflows with polling (DSAR, Cohorts, Event Streaming Metrics)
- S3 pre-signed URLs for large data transfers
- Webhook-style attribution with 72-hour matching windows
- Real-time profile enrichment for personalization

## Key API Endpoints and Operations

**Primary Ingestion:**
- `POST api2.amplitude.com/2/httpapi` - Event ingestion
- `POST api2.amplitude.com/batch` - Bulk event upload
- `POST api2.amplitude.com/identify` - User property updates
- `POST api2.amplitude.com/attribution` - Attribution events

**Data Access:**
- `GET api.amplitude.com/api/2/export` - Raw data export
- `GET profile-api.amplitude.com/v1/userprofile` - User profiles
- Various Dashboard REST endpoints for analytics queries

**Management Operations:**
- `GET/POST api.amplitude.com/api/3/cohorts` - Cohort management
- `GET/POST/PUT/DELETE data-api.amplitude.com/api/3/lookup_table` - Lookup tables
- `GET/POST/PUT/DELETE api.amplitude.com/api/2/taxonomy` - Schema management

The platform supports comprehensive analytics workflows from data collection through analysis, user management, and compliance, with enterprise-grade features for large-scale deployments and strict data governance requirements.